        <div class="accordion-body">
          <strong>The primary goal is to promote resource efficiency, reduce waste, and foster sustainable practices throughout every stage of production and consumption. This involves creating systems that maximize the use of resources, minimize environmental impact, and prioritize renewable, recyclable, or biodegradable materials. Moreover, this initiative seeks to raise awareness of the critical social inequalities that contribute to and exacerbate unsustainable practices. By recognizing and addressing these disparities—such as unequal access to sustainable products, fair wages, and safe working conditions—the approach aims to build a more inclusive, equitable system where the environmental and social well-being of all communities is prioritized. This holistic perspective encourages responsible choices from both producers and consumers, ultimately fostering a culture of sustainability that supports long-term environmental health and social justice.</strong>
        </div>
