  <section id="consumers">
  <div class="stats-section">
    <h2>What can we do as costumers?</h2>
    <p>As consumers, we can contribute to a sustainable and responsible lifestyle by making informed choices that prioritize eco-friendly products and practices. <strong>Every small action counts, and together, we can drive meaningful change towards sustainability</strong>.</p>
    <div class="stats-cards">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <h3>Choose sustainable products</h3>
        <p>Opt for goods made from environmentally friendly materials, such as organic, recycled, or biodegradable
            options. Look for certifications like Fair Trade, which ensure that products are ethically produced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <h3>Support local and ethical brands:</h3>
        <p>Prioritize buying from businesses that are transparent about their supply chains and who treat their
            workers fairly. By supporting local brands, you can reduce your carbon footprint and help boost your local
            economy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <h3>Buy less, buy better:</h3>
        <p>Instead of focusing on quantity, invest in quality products that are durable and designed to last. This
            reduces waste and ensures that the items you buy are worth the investment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
